text: Critical response[edit] Ouija: Origin of Evil received positive reviews from critics, with many praising it as an improvement over its predecessor. On review aggregator website Rotten Tomatoes, the film has an approval rating of 81%, based on 72 reviews, with an average rating of 6.1/10. The site's critical consensus reads, "Ouija: Origin of Evil swerves its franchise's planchette unexpectedly to YES with a surprisingly scary and dramatically satisfying follow-up to its lackluster predecessor."[14] On Metacritic, which assigns a normalized rating, the film has a score 65 out of 100, based on 23 critics, indicating "generally favorable reviews".[15]

text: Anyone else going to watch this movie just for the director Mike Flanagan?  Check out his film Absentia - creepy af.  Not for everyone though, low budget indie, so many will just find it "slow".  However, for those like me who prefer creepy, slow burn, psychological horror, with flawed, realistic, and sympathetic characters behaving like human beings actually might behave in an extraordinary, horrific situation, you're in for a treat.  It gives me hope for this one, despite being underwhelmed by the first one (Olivia was nice to look at, though!).  Been busy, but I hope to see it tomorrow.  He also directed Oculus, Before I Wake, and Hush.  And no, I'm not him, you cynical bastards lol

For the longest time I would not sleep I would not eat, I just isolated myself. I was so afraid and I thought I was crazy lol. I don't see those things anymore though.. which is good. I would see my wrists cut open, and blood on the sink I would see people's skin turned inside out.. and I sometimes saw myself hanging on a rope, but slowly as I looked at myself my mouth was slowly carving open into a smile. then my eyes opened they were black.. excorsist things came through my head if I tried to sleep. nightmares all the time non-stop. I even had voices in my head telling me to kill myself. I did some crazy things before those pills came along I looked up satanic rituals. and it thought maybe that was my issue because ever since I've done that I became really depressed and suicidal. but now things have changed I still have my self doubt and still feel like I'm not worth anything but I'm atleast off that medication. thanks to the hospital they proceeded to tell me that I was not crazy and that nothing was wrong with me it was only that the medicine did not go well with me and they also said that most of the people that take that medicine almost commit suicide.
author: Katie Wilson
